<p>BioMed Central today
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://blogs.openaccesscentral.com/blogs/bmcblog/entry/hmmi_to_centrally_fund_publications">announced</ext-link>
that the
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://www.hhmi.org/">Howard
Hughes Medical Institute</ext-link> will become a BioMed Central member
(read the HHMI announcement
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://www.hhmi.org/news/bmc20070820.html">here</ext-link>).
HHMI will pay all article processing charges for HHMI investigators in
BioMed Central journals starting September 1.</p>
<p>This announcement comes two months after HHMI
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://www.hhmi.org/news/20070626.html">started
to require</ext-link> that all HHMI-supported research has to become
publicly available 6 months after publication and at a time when Yale
University
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://network.nature.com/blogs/user/mfenner/2007/08/05/yale-university-drops-biomed-central-membership">drops</ext-link>
their BioMed Central membership.</p>
<p>In
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120610115631/http://www.hhmi.org/news/hhmielsevier20070308.html">March</ext-link>
HHMI announced that all research published in Elsevier journals will be
publicly available 6 months after publication, again starting September
1.</p>
<p>Congratulations HHMI.</p>
